I had an opportunity to use new HONOR Magic5 Pro for a short period. I was amazed by its photo and video capabilities ( some photos coming soon) but the best feature regarding video is its MOVIE mode that allows you to shoot 10 bit Log that is amazing to grade. Just incredible. And look at the bokeh, the main camera really gives amazing footage both in video and photo with it’s 1/1.2” sensor and f1.6 lens.

Capturing the power and passion of the Wings for Life World Run through my lens is a humbling experience that I anticipate each year. This global race is a melting pot of inspiration, drawing individuals from every corner of the world, united in their quest to run for those who can't.

As a member of the Red Bull Photography team, I am entrusted not only with capturing the perfect shot but weaving the heartfelt stories of the runners, their relentless spirit, and the extraordinary cause they champion. It's not just a race, it's a celebration of humanity, resilience, and our collective power to bring about a positive change.

The smiles, the grit, the determination that paints every face, follows me throughout the entire race. The energy is palpable, pushing you to your limits, and yet, the overwhelming emotions make the hard work feel incredibly rewarding.

But what makes Wings for Life World Run exceptional is the cause it supports. Every step taken, every sweat dropped is a stride towards a cure for spinal cord injuries. The event is more than just a race; it's a mission that is deeply embedded in our hearts.

Being a part of this incredible initiative feels like a privilege. Our photographs are not just images; they are powerful narratives that help amplify the voice of Wings for Life World Run and its pursuit of finding a cure.

The emotional impact of being part of this event transcends far beyond the race day. It's a testament to the fact that when we stand together, when we unite for a common cause, we can indeed move mountains. #wingsforlifeworldrun #runforthosewhocant #redbullphotography

I borrowed Fuji x100v from my pal @alexander.starbuck just to see what’s the hype about it. And I have to say now I understand and it is not the colors or image quality I can get the same with any of my canon cameras. It is the size and the enjoyment that the process of using it provides. It is the closest I came with any digital camera to the feeling of shooting film. This camera is just extremely fun to use for everyday snaps. Here are few 😊
Do you have a similar camera? Camera that is just fun to use? 
#fujix100v #croatia_photography #fujifilm_xseries
